title.narrative: Capacities of Child protection actors and services providers strengthened to better protect vulnerable children from abuse,violence and exploitation

description.narrative: Enhancing national capacities was a priority in 2021. UNICEF continued to build national capacity to implement an effective child protection case management system and to reinforce the capacity of service providers, with 3,328 professionals (2,095 females) including front-line workers, service providers and teachers trained. The capacity building focused on providing quality services including community-based interventions, case management, gender-based violence (GBV) and EORE. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:16/01/2022
